00:00:13.170 --> 00:00:15.270
So what are these financial markets?

00:00:15.690 --> 00:00:20.700
Think of them as a massive buzzing
marketplace, a network where people and

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:26.820
big organizations buy and sell financial
assets like stocks, bonds, and currencies.

00:00:27.330 --> 00:00:29.520
It's like a giant pipeline for money.

00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:34.410
Moving it from those who have extra
stashed away the savers to those who

00:00:34.410 --> 00:00:38.575
desperately need it, like businesses
wanting to expand or borrowers.

00:00:39.349 --> 00:00:43.129
Now within this huge marketplace,
there is a very important

00:00:43.129 --> 00:00:45.019
section called capital Markets.

00:00:45.410 --> 00:00:48.290
This part deals only with long-term funds.

00:00:48.559 --> 00:00:53.000
We are talking about money that is lent
or invested for more than one year.

00:00:53.449 --> 00:00:57.709
The two main stars of this show are
the stock market where company shares

00:00:57.709 --> 00:01:01.400
are traded, and the bond market
where debt instruments get traded.

00:01:01.930 --> 00:01:06.130
These are absolutely crucial for
businesses to raise big money for

00:01:06.130 --> 00:01:10.240
long-term projects and for governments
to get the funds for their spending.

00:01:10.780 --> 00:01:12.730
Now, real world relevance.

00:01:13.150 --> 00:01:17.260
Now, why should you even bother
with all this in the banking sector?

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:21.070
Understanding these markets is
vital for managing financial

00:01:21.070 --> 00:01:23.230
products and services effectively.

00:01:23.649 --> 00:01:28.779
For your investment decisions, it helps
you assess credit risks and make informed

00:01:28.779 --> 00:01:33.910
recommendations to clients that won't come
back to haunt you for client advisory.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.770
This knowledge allows you to advise
clients on investment opportunities based

00:01:38.770 --> 00:01:40.839
on what the market is actually doing.

00:01:41.259 --> 00:01:46.000
And finally, for risk management, it
helps you make sound financial decisions

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:50.470
within the bank by understanding both
market risks and golden opportunities.

