00:02:57.234 --> 00:03:01.375
The capital market deals with
long-term funds like equity and

00:03:01.375 --> 00:03:02.875
debt for more than one year.

00:03:03.295 --> 00:03:06.984
The money market is its energetic
cousin dealing with short-term

00:03:06.990 --> 00:03:08.515
funds for less than a year.

00:03:08.915 --> 00:03:12.575
The primary market is where new
securities are issued for the

00:03:12.575 --> 00:03:14.855
very first time, like an IPOs.

00:03:15.275 --> 00:03:19.625
The secondary market is where these
already existing securities are traded

00:03:19.625 --> 00:03:22.355
among investors like on stock exchanges.

00:03:22.745 --> 00:03:26.735
SEBI is the Securities and
Exchange Board of India, the big

00:03:26.765 --> 00:03:28.595
regulator for capital markets.

00:03:28.925 --> 00:03:33.335
The RBI or Reserve Bank of India
is our central bank regulating

00:03:33.335 --> 00:03:34.960
money markets and all of banking.

00:03:35.705 --> 00:03:38.375
An IPO is an initial public offering.

00:03:38.465 --> 00:03:44.315
The first time a company offers its
shares to the public, FII or FBI stands

00:03:44.315 --> 00:03:48.635
for Foreign Institutional Investor or
Foreign Portfolio Investor, which are

00:03:48.665 --> 00:03:54.215
overseas groups investing in our markets
and gex are simply government securities

00:03:54.275 --> 00:03:56.555
bonds issued by the government itself.

