00:05:39.725 --> 00:05:41.915
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:05:42.245 --> 00:05:44.675
Be careful to avoid some common traps.

00:05:44.945 --> 00:05:49.055
A very frequent error is confusing
the money market and capital market.

00:05:49.235 --> 00:05:53.345
Just remember, money market is
short-term, capital market is long-term.

00:05:53.675 --> 00:05:56.525
Another is misidentifying
regulatory bodies.

00:05:56.705 --> 00:06:00.065
Please don't attribute capital
market regulation to RBI

00:06:00.065 --> 00:06:01.565
or money markets to sebi.

00:06:01.715 --> 00:06:02.600
It's the other way around.

00:06:03.335 --> 00:06:06.455
People also mix up the
primary and secondary markets.

00:06:06.575 --> 00:06:09.005
The primary market is only for new issues.

00:06:09.185 --> 00:06:13.955
Also, don't forget the long-term nature
of capital markets, which means funds

00:06:13.955 --> 00:06:18.725
for more than one year and never, ever
overlook the basic definitions of terms.

